window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>The worst villain any Beaufont has ever faced has just stepped out of the shadows.</b> Genevieve Beaufont can't hide from the evil that's unveiled itself. <b>And no one can believe who it is.</b></p> <p>It has been foretold that when Gen's true nemesis revealed themselves that this would launch her into her ultimate role. It is time for this medieval warrior to rule over the world of magic—having ultimate domain.</p> <p><b>Besides from the gods, who started this all, no one is more powerful than Gen and her dragon, Emperor.</b></p> <p>That's why one man wants to stop her. Gen simply can't <i>have</i> her title. She must <i>fight</i> for it.</p> <p>Everything has been building towards this. No war will be more epic than this one—when the final fight happens for the throne to rule over magic.</p> <p><b>Can Gen Beaufont defend her role, taking supreme authority?</b> Or will this ancient evil stop her, stealing dominion and taking over all. She must fight for this role or watch as tyranny reigns over the world.</p> <p><b>Mother Nature and Father Time can no longer help. They've chosen their player. Now, it's time for them to sit back and watch the game of life unfurl.</b> The future of the world of magic and mortals ultimately depends on who wins this war.</p>"; 
